updating the file permsision on a remote client using the module "file" , ansible playbook


---
- name: file permission update on remote client
  hosts: all
  tasks:
  
    - name : file permission update
      file:
        path: /home/abhi/linux1
        mode: 0666
      
      
      
      
      
      permission of the file updated
      
      To do the syntax check:
      
      ansible-playbook --syntax-check filepermssion.yml
      ansible-playbook -C filpermission.yml (dry run)
    
